This paper focuses on time synchronization in wireless sensor networks, which is a topic related to network protocols and communication. Therefore, cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture) is the most likely category. The paper also deals with energy efficiency, which is a concern in distributed computing, leading to cs.DC (Distributed, Parallel, and Cluster Computing) being a likely category as well. The paper involves the use of measurement data and estimation, which falls under cs.SY (Systems and Control) and cs.IT (Information Theory). Finally, the paper uses simulation results to verify the proposed scheme, which is related to machine learning and data analysis, leading to cs.LG (Machine Learning) being a possible category.
